# Local dev secrets for `wrangler dev`. Copy to .dev.vars and
# fill in values. The .dev.vars file is gitignored so your
# real secrets never land in the repo.
#
#   cp .dev.vars.example .dev.vars
#   # then edit .dev.vars with real values
#
# Production secrets live in `wrangler secret` (not here).
# See docs/DEPLOY.md "secrets" section for the full provisioning
# flow + rotation protocol.

# Resend transactional email API key. Used by /api/signup to
# send confirmation emails. When unset, signup falls through
# to DB-only (OK for smoke testing / dogfood, NOT for prod).
# Get a dev key at https://resend.com/api-keys and prefix with
# "re_".
RESEND_API_KEY=

# Reply-to address for confirmation emails. Must be verified
# in the Resend dashboard. In local dev any address is fine —
# emails still go through Resend's sandbox for dev keys.
RESEND_FROM_ADDRESS=info@brunny.ai

# Shared secret for /api/admin/* endpoints (signup-stats etc).
# Generate a random 32+ char value for local dev — anything
# long enough to prove caller intent. When unset, admin
# endpoints return 503 (honest "not provisioned") NOT 401
# (denied). This is intentional: the R1 round-trip dogfood
# surfaced the distinction as a compliance signal.
#
# Example: openssl rand -hex 32
ADMIN_TOKEN=
